## 🖥️ Window & Virtual Canvas System

```python
VWIDTH, VHEIGHT = 1000, 600        # virtual resolution I draw on
canvas = pygame.Surface(...)        # internal drawing surface
screen = pygame.display.set_mode(..., pygame.RESIZABLE)  # real window
```

**The Problem I Solved:**
If I draw directly on the screen, the game breaks when the user resizes the window — buttons move, characters shift position, everything goes wrong.

**My Solution — Virtual Canvas:**
- I always draw everything on a fixed 1000×600 surface called `canvas`
- Then I scale that canvas to fit whatever size the real window is
- The player can resize the window freely and everything stays in the right place

**3 helper functions that make this work:**

| Function | What it does |
|---|---|
| `scale_pos(pos)` | Converts real mouse coordinates → virtual canvas coordinates |
| `blit_canvas()` | Scales canvas → fits real window with black bars (letterbox) |
| `get_events()` | Grabs all pygame events and fixes mouse positions using `scale_pos` |

