## 🌌 draw_space()

```python
def draw_space():
    canvas.fill((10, 10, 30))       # dark navy background
    for s in stars:
        pygame.draw.circle(...)     # draw each star
        s[1] += 1                   # move star downward
        if s[1] > VHEIGHT:          # if off screen, reset to top
            s[0] = random.randint(0, VWIDTH)
            s[1] = 0
```

- 120 stars are placed randomly when the game starts
- Every frame, each star moves down 1 pixel
- When a star goes off the bottom, it reappears at a random position at the top
- Creates an infinite scrolling space effect with zero extra files

