## 🧑‍🎤 draw_player() — 9 Costumes, 1 Function

**This was a fun design challenge.** I needed to draw 9 different character looks without writing 9 separate functions.

**My solution — palette dictionary:**
```python
palettes = {
    "alien":    dict(body=(50,200,80), ear=..., eye=..., pupil=..., ...),
    "santa":    dict(body=RED,         ear=..., ...),
    "robot":    dict(body=(170,170,190), ...),
    # ... 9 costumes total
}
p = palettes.get(costume, palettes["alien"])  # pick the right colours
```

- The base body shape is always the same (rectangle + ear triangles + eyes + nose + mouth)
- The colours come from the palette lookup
- Each costume then gets its own **detail overlay** drawn on top (e.g. Santa gets a hat, Robot gets a chest panel, Clown gets rainbow hair)
- Adding a new costume = just add one entry to the dictionary + one `elif` block for its details

