## 🏠 home_screen()

The first screen the player sees. Contains:
- Animated star background (via `draw_space()`)
- Game title text
- A live character preview (via `draw_player()`) showing the current costume
- 3 buttons: PLAY → goes to `level_select()`, COSTUME → goes to `costume_menu()`, QUIT → exits
- Dev mode badge (only visible when `DEVELOPER_MODE = True`)

**Game loop pattern used here (same in all screens):**
```python
while True:
    clock.tick(FPS)       # limit to 60 frames per second
    draw_space()          # redraw background every frame
    # ... draw all UI ...
    for event in get_events():
        # handle clicks
    blit_canvas()         # push canvas to real window
```

